A torus is a surface of revolution generated by revolving a circle in three-dimensional space one full revolution about an axis that is coplanar with the circle. \n\nThe \"major radius\" is the distance of the center of the tube to the center of the whole object.
A percentage is a number or ratio expressed as a fraction of 100
Roman numerals are a numeral system that originated in ancient Rome and remained the usual way of writing numbers throughout Europe well into the Late Middle Ages
Modulo is a system of arithmetic for integers, where numbers \"wrap around\" when reaching a certain value, called the modulus
Radical is an unresolved root, especially one using the radical symbol

Prime number is a number greater than 1 that is not a product of two smaller natural numbers.
Even numbers are those numbers that are completely divisible by 2.
Odd number is a number that is not divisible by 2.
A linear equation is an algebraic equation of the form y=mx+b
A ratio shows how many times one number contains another
Clock angle problems are a type of mathematical problem which involve finding the angle between the hands of an analog clock
Probability of an event is a number that indicates how likely the event is to occur
A fraction represents a part of a whole or, more generally, any number of equal parts

Combination and permutation are two different ways of grouping elements of a set into subsets. In a combination, the elements of the subset can be listed in any order. In a permutation, the elements of the subset are listed in a specific order.

Coin flipping or coin tossing is the practice of throwing a coin in the air and checking which side is showing when it lands, in order to choose between two alternatives, heads or tails, sometimes used to resolve a dispute between two parties
Dice are thrown to provide random numbers
Binomial Coefficients are the positive integers that occur as coefficients in the binomial theorem
Gamma function is a generalization of the factorial function to non-integer numbers
Fabric is material produced by weaving together cotton, nylon, wool, silk, or other threads
Body mass index is a value derived from the mass and height of a person. It is used to screen for weight categories that may lead to health problems
Body Surface Area is the measured or calculated surface area of a human body
Waist Ratio is the dimensionless ratio of the circumference of the waist and has been used as an indicator or measure of health, fertility, and the risk of developing serious health conditions
Cardiac Index is a haemodynamic parameter that relates the cardiac output from left ventricle in one minute to body surface area, thus relating heart performance to the size of the individual
Lean Body Mass is a measure of a person\'s weight without fat
Relative Fat Mass (RFM) is an index used to estimate body fat percentage based on waist circumference, height, and biological sex
FFMI is an alternative to body mass index which accounts for a person\'s muscle mass. \n\nNote: this app uses US Navy method.
Calcium Correction calculates a corrected calcium level for patients with hypoalbuminemia
Friction is the force resisting the relative motion of solid surfaces, fluid layers, and material elements sliding against each other
Pressure is the force applied perpendicular to the surface of an object per unit area over which that force is distributed
Acceleration is the rate of change of the velocity of an object with respect to time
Displacement is a vector whose length is the shortest distance from the initial to the final position of a point P undergoing motion

Velocity is the directional speed of an object in motion as an indication of its rate of change in position as observed from a particular frame of reference and as measured by a particular standard of time
Einstein Theory of Relativity is the relationship between mass and energy in a system\'s rest frame, where the two quantities differ only by a multiplicative constant and the units of measurement
Lorentz Factor or Lorentz term is a quantity expressing how much the measurements of time, length, and other physical properties change for an object while that object is moving
Molar concentration is a measure of the concentration of a chemical species, in particular of a solute in a solution, in terms of amount of substance per unit volume of solution
Mach Number is a dimensionless quantity in fluid dynamics representing the ratio of flow velocity past a boundary to the local speed of sound
Parabola is a plane curve which is mirror-symmetrical and is approximately U-shaped
The Koch Curve is a fractal curve and one of the earliest fractals to have been described
Helix is a shape like a corkscrew or spiral staircase. It is a type of smooth space curve with tangent lines at a constant angle to a fixed axis
Ellipsoid is a 3D geometric figure that has an elliptical shape
Spherical Segment is the solid defined by cutting a sphere or a ball with a pair of parallel planes
Spherical Cap is the region of a sphere which lies above (or below) a given plane
Sphere is a geometrical object that is a three-dimensional analogue to a two-dimensional circle
Cylinder is a 3D solid shape that consists of two identical and parallel bases linked by a curved surface
Conical Frustum is a frustum created by slicing the top off a cone
Cone is a three-dimensional geometric shape that tapers smoothly from a flat base to a point called the apex or vertex
Pyramid is a polyhedron formed by connecting a polygonal base and a point, called the apex
Pyramidal Frustum is a frustum made by chopping the top off a pyramid

Prism is a polyhedron comprising an n-sided polygon base, a second base which is a translated copy of the first, and n other faces, necessarily all parallelograms, joining corresponding sides of the two bases
Cube is a three-dimensional solid object bounded by six square faces, facets or sides, with three meeting at each vertex
Ellipse is a plane curve surrounding two focal points, such that for all points on the curve, the sum of the two distances to the focal points is a constant
The arc of a circle is defined as the part or segment of the circumference of a circle
Pentagon is any five-sided polygon or 5-gon
Rhombus is a quadrilateral whose four sides all have the same length
Trapezium is a quadrilateral that has at least one pair of parallel sides
Square is a regular quadrilateral, which means that it has four equal sides and four equal angles
Right Triangle is a triangle in which one angle is a right angle (that is, a 90-degree angle), i.e., in which two sides are perpendicular
Triangle is a polygon with three edges and three vertices
Rectangle is a quadrilateral with four right angles
Circle is a closed two-dimensional figure in which the set of all the points in the plane is equidistant from a given point called “center”
Electric power is the rate at which electrical energy is transferred by an electric circuit
Heat capacity or thermal capacity is a physical property of matter, defined as the amount of heat to be supplied to an object to produce a unit change in its temperature
The ideal gas law, also called the general gas equation, is the equation of state of a hypothetical ideal gas
Energy Efficiency is the ratio of energy output to energy input
Aquarium is a vivarium of any size having at least one transparent side in which aquatic plants or animals are kept and displayed

If you see multi zeros at the result, it means that your answer is out of system\'s limit. It occurred because Android libraries only support 64-bit calculation. If you need to calculate long numbers, you can go to General Calculations and open Long Basic Calculator.

A force is an influence that can cause an object to change its velocity, i.e., to accelerate, unless counterbalanced by other forces.
Urea-to-creatinine ratio, known in the United States as BUN-to-creatinine ratio, is the ratio of the blood levels of urea and creatinine.\n\nNote: on this app, 1 mg/dL = 0.3571 mmol/L.
The anion gap is a value calculated from the results of multiple individual medical lab tests.
Iron deficiency anemia is the most common cause of anemia worldwide, which results in microcytic and hypochromic red cells on the peripheral smear.

Transferrin Saturation (TS) is the value of serum iron divided by the total iron-binding capacity of the available transferrin, the main protein that binds iron in the blood, this value tells a clinician how much serum iron is bound.

The QT interval is a measurement made on an electrocardiogram used to assess some of the electrical properties of the heart. The QT interval changes in response to the heart rate - as heart rate increase the QT interval shortens. These changes make it harder to compare QT intervals measured at different heart rates. To account for this, and thereby improve the reliability of QT measurement, the QT interval can be corrected for heart rate (QTc) using a variety of mathematical formulae, a process often performed automatically by modern ECG recorders.
The serum-ascites albumin gradient (SAAG) is a medical value representing the albumin concentration difference between blood serum and the ascitic fluid.
Low-density lipoproteins is the complex particles that carry lipids in the blood.
Avogadro\'s number is the number of particles in a mole. Equal to 6.02214076 × 10²³
Concentration describes the composition of a solution.
Water heating is a heat transfer process that uses an energy source to heat water above its initial temperature.
Cannot calculate water that already boiled
Frequency is the number of completed wave cycles per second.
A resistance to the hormone insulin, resulting in increasing blood sugar.
Bond order is a formal measure of the multiplicity of a covalent bond between two atoms.
Neutralization or neutralisation is a chemical reaction in which acid and a base react with an equivalent quantity of each other. The result of this reaction is the formation of a salt.
Cofunction is a trigonometric function whose value for the complement of an angle is equal to the value of a given trigonometric function of the angle itself.
